result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

14CM-239, 14CM-399, 15CF-115, 16CF-138 and 16CM-252 - All Cases Called @ 10:37 AM: Defendant Kiven Todd Luebke in court, in custody, with attorney John H. Wallace, both appearing in person.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Per DA:  State will conceded to 134 days TS credit from 6/28 thru today.   Global resolution recited by DA with argued terms on SEH.  Atty Wallace confirms there will not be a request for PSI today.  Def and counsel confirm State's recital on resolution.  16CF-138:  Court entertains waiver of pre-lim hearing.  Court accepts knowing and voluntary waiver of the pre-lim hearing in its entirety.  Def BOT.  INFO Filed - INFO Stated - Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.   Defendant advised of potential punishment as to all 3 charges.  Terms of bifurcated SEH explained.   Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  16CF-138:  Plea:  NC  16CM-252:  Plea Cts 3 & 4:  NC   Court accepts pleas and enters JOC to all 3 Counts.  Cts 1,2,5&6 of 16CM-252, 14CM-239, 14CM-399 and 15CF-115 all DRI.  Court addresses Def as to any request for PSI.   Def waives PSI and Court accepts knowing and voluntary waiver of PSI by DOC.  State also confirms will not be requesting a PSI by DOC.  Argument by DA Blader - argues for prison SEH with consecutive probation.  Argument by Atty Wallace.  Statement by Def prior to SEH:  None offered.  The Court:  16CF-138:  40 mos Bifurcated SEH - 16 mos IC/24 mos ES 134 days TS credit against term of imprisonment.  Not appropriate for CIP/SAP and declines eligibility.  Conditions of ES and supervision:  Comply in total with all SORP requirements, the defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician, AODA and any follow thru, Maintain full time gainful employment unless a physician places a work limitation upon the Defendant; Costs of each case.  16CM-252:  S/W - 2 yrs probation Cts 3 and 4 - consecutive to 16CF-138 term of imprisonment.  DNA Sample (already on file per bailiff) and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.  Appeal Rights Given.
Plea/sentencing hearing on November 9, 2016 at 10:30 am.

14CM-239, 14CM-339, 15CF-115 and 16CM-252 - All Cases Called @ 12:47 PM: Defendant Kiven Todd Luebke in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi, both appearing via video.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  All Complaints Stated.  ADA argues as to significant cash bond in the area of $5-10,000.00 - outstanding warrants in other jurisdiction and flight risk exists.  Statement as to bond by SPD - no position taken on bond request.  ADA elaborates as to conditions of bond being requested.  Court reviews statutory authority cited by the State.  Upon review of the statute, the Court believes that pursuant to s. 968.38(2) a formal application must be made for the blood draw.  State will file proper motion for further hearing.  Riverside Ruling made.   AIA scheduled and also STC scheduled as to 14CM-239.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for July 12, 2016 at 01:15 pm.
